<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Page x:Class="SpeedyBee.Pages.AboutPage"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      Title="About">

    <StackPanel Margin="20">
        <TextBlock Text="About SpeedyBee"
                   FontSize="24"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="0,0,0,20"/>

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap"
                   Margin="0,0,0,20">
            <Run>SpeedyBee is an advanced line follower robot project designed specifically for</Run>
            <Run FontWeight="Bold">the RoboChallenge 2025</Run>
            <Run>competition. The project combines cutting-edge sensor technology with sophisticated control algorithms to achieve precise line following capabilities. It uses an IMU together with line sensors to follow a marked path, designed with low-cost components to demonstrate efficient motion control within a limited budget.</Run>
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock Text="Key Features"
                   FontSize="18"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="0,20,0,10"/>

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap"
                   Margin="0,0,0,20">
            - Line following control using a PD algorithm
            - Real-time IMU data visualization through a companion app
            - Tuned for stable and accurate movement during competition
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock Text="Components"
                   FontSize="18"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="0,20,0,10"/>

        <StackPanel Margin="0,0,0,20">
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Microcontroller:</Run> Marble Pico (Main controller handling sensors and motor control)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Motor Driver:</Run> DRV8243 (Controls motor speed and direction)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Power:</Run> 3S LiPo battery (Power supply)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">IMU Sensor:</Run> Bosch BMI 323 (Gyroscope and accelerometer module)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Line Sensors:</Run> JSumo XLine 16 (Reflective sensors)
            </TextBlock>
            <TextBlock>
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Motors:</Run> NovaMax 450 RPM (DC motors for movement)
            </TextBlock>
        </StackPanel>

        <TextBlock Text="Future Improvements"
                   FontSize="18"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="0,20,0,10"/>

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap"
                   Margin="0,0,0,20">
            - Improve power efficiency and battery management
            - Expand visualization features (e.g., web or PC interface)
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock Text="Acknowledgements"
                   FontSize="18"
                   FontWeight="Bold"
                   Margin="0,20,0,10"/>

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap"
                   Margin="0,0,0,20">
            This project was developed for RoboChallenge 2025 as a practical implementation of control systems and sensor fusion. The focus was on building a functional, affordable, and tunable robot using easily available components.
        </TextBlock>

